Alexander Bolshunov of the Russian Olympic Committee Photo: VCGSix Olympic competitions of February 6 were completed and here is a summary of the results and medal winners. Final of men's 15km + 15km Skiathlon of Cross-Country Skiing ended on Monday afternoon, Alexander Bolshunov of the ROC, 25, won the gold medal with Denis Spitsov who is also from Russia and Finnish athlete Iivo Niskanen coming in second and third place respectively. In Bolshunov's debut at the Pyeongchang 2018 Olympic Winter Games, he became a four-time medalist. In the women's snowboard slopestyle final, New Zealand's Zoi Sadowski-Synnott, 20, topping the podium with a score of 92.88, while Julia Marino from the US and Australian athlete Tess Coady winning the silver medal and bronze medal respectively.Nils Göran van der Poel from Sweden won the gold medal at the men's 5,000m speed skating.In the men's normal hill individual final, Ryoyu Kubayashi from Japan bagged the gold.The winner of men's luge was Johannes Ludwig from Germany. Jakara Anthony from Australia won gold in women's moguls of freestyle skiing.